"But let us consider the secret reasons which Vir- gil had for thus framing this noble episode, wherein the whole passion of love is more exactly described, than in any other poet. Love was the theme of his fourth book : and though it is the shortest of the whole /Eneis, yet there he has given its beginning, its progress, its traverses, and its conclusion ; and had exhausted so entirely this subject, that he could resume it but very slightly in the eight ensuing books."